OL,7,FStephanie Taylor, whose son Haydn, 12,
OL,8,Fis autistic, told ITV News West
OL,9,FCountry: "All we're trying to do is
OL,10,Fmake sure they get the same as any
OL,11,Fother child would.
OL,13,F"I don't know what Haydn's future is
OL,14,Fgoing to be like. It is hard, and it's
OL,15,Fmade harder by having to fight for
OL,16,Feverything."
OL,18,FPlymouth City Council is in the
OL,19,Fprocess of preparing its yearly budget
OL,20,Fand Stephanie is worried that they are
OL,21,Fspending money in all the wrong places.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
