OL,3,CMum of autistic boy fears for his
OL,4,Cfuture as council faces budget
OL,5,Cpressures
OL,7,FOwner Cindy Willcocks said: "There
OL,8,Fwill always be those people that need
OL,9,Fto go into residential homes or
OL,10,Fnursing homes, and we need to make
OL,11,Fprovision for that.
OL,13,F"It does require people working
OL,14,Ftogether. As individuals, people try
OL,15,Fto do the best they can with the
OL,16,Fskills and knowledge they've got and
OL,17,Fthe budgets they've got.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
